                <h4 style="padding-top:10px;">Olympic Lanes</h4>
                <ul class="plain-list">
                    <li>Olympic Lanes will be open for accredited vehicles only. They will be identified with signs. Unaccredited vehicles cannot drive in these lanes for the duration of the Games.
                    </li>
                    <li>24 hours a day, 7 days a week
                    </li>
                    <li>From January 24th until March 30th 2014</li>
                </ul><br />
                <h4>Transportation Filters</h4>
                <ul class="plain-list">
                    <li>Two police officers will be responsible to control the vehicle access to the Olympic Lanes
                    </li><li>They will also redirect the vehicles without an official Sochi 2014 Vehicle Access and Parking Permit (VAPP) to the appropriate road
                    </li>
                </ul><br />
                <h4>Self-Driving</h4>
                <ul class="plain-list">
                    <li>Non-Russian citizens will require the following in order to drive in Russia:
                    </li><li>International Passport
                    </li><li>National Driving License (with an International  Driving Permit) or
                    </li><li>National Driving License (with a certified translation)
                    </li><li><a href="http://www.caa.ca/idp/" target="_blank">Click here</a> to learn more about obtaining an International Driving Permit
                    </li>
                </ul>
